      "weather": "Overcast",
      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FEDERAL SENOR (8) proved too good on debut over 388m at Gosford to score by 4 lengths (22.20). Boxed wide but has the pace to be prominent. Tougher here but can go on with it. RITZA ROCKER (1) is struggling to break through but racing consistently, finishing in the minors three starts on end. Last time out flew the lids with a fast early sectional but gathered in and finished in the minors when second (22.93) at this track over 400m. Will give a great sight again. ELLA'S GLORY (2) missed the frame last time when eighth (20.01) at Bulli but prior to that had two placings in a row. Solid record at the distance winning two races. Cannot be taken lightly. MIDNIGHT MOHAWK (7) looks an each-way chance.",
